  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Tampere Traumatic head and brain injury study is a prospective study aiming to explore
      neuroradiological, neuropsychological, neurological and biochemical aspects of mild
      traumatic brain injury (mtbi). The main interest is on factors that effect to the outcome
      after mtbi. The study is conducted in Tampere University Hospital's emergency department
      between the 1st of August 2010 and 31st of July 2013.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Aims of the study:

        1. To improve clinical assessment of mTBI in the acute phase

        2. To assemble better knowledge of diffusion tensor imaging as a diagnostic tool in mTBI

        3. To improve neuropsychological evaluation of mTBI Main focus on psychosocial functioning
           / outcome / correlates E.g. Resilience, PTSD
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
